@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About";
}

<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>
    This application is built using <strong>ASP.NET Core MVC</strong> with
    <strong>Identity Framework</strong> to provide secure authentication, session
    management, and user access control.
</p>

<h3>About This Application</h3>
<p>
    The purpose of this project is to demonstrate a modern, secure, and scalable
    web application built using Microsoft technologies. The system includes:
</p>

<ul>
    <li>User registration and login</li>
    <li>Role-based authentication</li>
    <li>Session-based user experience</li>
    <li>Database-driven storage using Entity Framework Core</li>
    <li>Fully responsive UI using Bootstrap</li>
</ul>

<h3>Technology Stack</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>ASP.NET Core MVC</strong></li>
    <li><strong>ASP.NET Core Identity</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Entity Framework Core</strong> (SQL Server)</li>
    <li><strong>C#</strong> for backend logic</li>
    <li><strong>Bootstrap</strong> for responsive design</li>
</ul>

<h3>Features</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Secure login & session handling</li>
    <li>User data protection and privacy settings</li>
    <li>Modular architecture for easy expansion</li>
    <li>Customizable layout and components</li>
</ul>

<h3>Developer Message</h3>
<p>
    This project is created to help developers learn and implement modern ASP.NET Core features,
    including Identity, session management, dependency injection, and Razor UI practices.
    The code is clean, modular, and ready for further customization.
</p>

<p>
    If you want to add more pages, features, or custom functionality, feel free to ask!
</p>
